    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-08-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-08-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="138"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d138">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 138.</note>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Davis</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Bancroft</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 223.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic"> Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-08-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 23, 1870.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    dispatch of the 27th ultimo, No. 118, inclosing a copy of a convention between
                    France and Prussia, alleged to have been proposed by M. Benedetti, the French
                    ambassador, having for its object the union of Germany and the annexation of
                    Belgium and Luxembourg to France.</p>
                <p>You are instructed to ascertain, if possible, from the minister of foreign
                    affairs, when the proposition for the convention was made, and why it was not
                    sooner made known.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. C. B. DAVIS, <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
